### **PROJECT OVERVIEW**


We are looking for a **Senior AI Technical Writer** to own documentation across the portfolio of audiology software products and tools. Working at the intersection of product knowledge, AI tooling, and communication, you will create and maintain customer-facing and internal documentation, including release notes, user guides, administrator guides, IFUs, and operational knowledge resources.  



**The role requires ability to travel across EU.**

### **IN THIS ROLE, YOU WILL**

* Own customer-facing product documentation and release communications – defining what gets communicated, at what level of detail, and in what voice across all products;
* Direct AI agents — write precise prompts and orchestrate agent pipelines to draft release documentation from ADO/Jira items, changelogs, and QA reports;
* Audit for accuracy — catch factual errors, hallucinations, version mismatches, and feature descriptions that don't reflect the shipped product;
* Calibrate for audience — adapt content for end users, clinic admins, and technical integrators; enforce the right depth and terminology for each;
* Maintain voice and brand — uphold the style across all customer-facing documentation. Partner with product and design teams to occasionally create and refine in-product UI text, microcopy, workflows, and user guidance, acting as a UI/UX writer when needed;
* Triage and scope — decide what crosses the threshold for public communication and build that policy into repeatable agent workflows;
* Manage source inputs — pull from and reconcile ADO/Jira tickets, QA sign-offs, product specs, and developer notes as inputs to the documentation pipeline;
* Improve processes — continuously refine prompt templates, review checklists, and tooling to raise quality and reduce cycle time;
* Manage translations and translated documentation — coordinate documentation localization across products, currently up to 16 languages per product, ensuring consistency, accuracy, and timely delivery of translated customer-facing content;
* Define and maintain documentation standards, templates, review processes, and best practices across products.

### **IF YOU ARE**

* 5+ years in technical writing, product documentation, or developer communications — ideally in a SaaS or healthcare software environment;
* Demonstrated experience using AI tools (LLMs, AI writing assistants, or agent workflows) in a production documentation context;
* Strong information architecture instincts — you know how to structure content for the reader, not the developer;
* Sharp accuracy auditing skills — you can spot a plausible-but-wrong feature description and know how to verify it;
* Experience working directly with product management and engineering in an agile/sprint environment;
* Familiarity with ADO, Jira, or similar issue-tracking systems as documentation source material;
* Excellent written English; concise, direct, and consistent under pressure of release cycles.

### **NICE TO HAVE**

* Experience in audiology, healthcare IT, or regulated software industries;
* Hands-on work with prompt engineering or custom AI agent configuration;
* Familiarity with docs-as-code workflows or structured authoring environments;
* Experience writing for multiple distinct audience segments from a single source;
* Experience managing translated documentation or localization workflows across multiple languages;
* Proficiency in one or more languages in addition to English.

### **HOW’S THE HIRING PROCESS GOING**


We strive to make our hiring process smooth and transparent to find the perfect match for both sides. Steps may differ depending on the role, but here’s what to expect:

* **Initial Interview:** If your background fits the role, we’ll invite you for an interview with a Talent Acquisition Specialist.
* **Technical Interview:**Depending on the position, you may complete a technical assessment or test task.
* **Client Interview**
* **Final Decision:** After all steps, we’ll get back to you with the result and next steps.
